+## v0.3.37 final GUI-preparation closeout contract
+
+Before GUI MVP implementation starts, the project must have a deterministic closeout record for the remaining standard-error classes discovered during v0.3.36 release/DOI work:
+
+- `release-check` is a pre-publication gate. After a tag or GitHub Release exists, use `post-release-check` and DOI/documentation verification instead.
+- `gh pr checks` returning no checks reported is a diagnostic state, not CI success. It must not be converted into `CI: PASS`.
+- After a gate failure, later mutation or merge sections must not run or appear as if they ran. Stop before PR creation, merge, tag, release, or branch switching that depends on the failed gate.
+- GUI preparation requires a zero direct `tools/ns_*.sh` adapter state, deterministic audit matrix coverage, typed work-order coverage, action registry coverage, terminal-log evidence discipline, and post-release gate separation.
